A Karmo Grade 1 Area Court, Abuja on Friday sentenced a woman, Amina Ali, to three month in prison for stealing 15 pieces of children’s clothes in an Abuja market. Ali, who lived in Masaka, Nasarawa State, pleaded guilty to theft and begged the court for leniency. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network “ I am so sorry for what I did; please sir, forgive me, this is my first time to steal and will never do it again’’ “I have four children and nobody is taking care of them right now’’ Ali pleaded. The Judge Alhaji Inuwa Maiwada convicted and sentenced Ali following her guilty plea and based on the facts of the case. Maiwada, however, gave Ali an option of N7, 000 fine and warned her to desist from crime. The Judge held that Ali, who was a first time offender, had begged the court for mercy. ”Sentencing you to three months in prison would make you to repent.” he held. The prosecution counsel, Ijeoma Ukagha, told the court that Nwafor Nneoma, who resides in Dutse Alhaji village, Abuja, reported the matter at the Utako Police Station on July 30 Ukagha said that at about 8 a.m Ali went into Nneoma’s shop at Utako Uttra modern Market, Abuja and pretended to buy cotton puds. She said that in the process the convict criminal and dishonestly stole 15 pieces of children’s clothes valued at N60,000 from the complainant’s shop. Ukagha informed the court that during investigation the convict confessed committed the crime and the stolen clothes were recovered from her. The prosecutor said that the offence contravened the provisions of Section 288 of the Penal Code. Following the plea of the convict, the prosecutor prayed the court to try him summarily under Section 347 of the Administration of Criminal Justices Act, 2015 (NAN)